# [[twenty]]

====Usage notes====
* Apart from liaison contexts, the final ''-t'' is pronounced in the compound numbers 21 to 29: {{m|fr|vingt-cinq}} {{IPAchar|/vɛ̃t.sɛ̃k/}}.
* In contrast, the final -t in ''vingt'' in 81 to 99 is never pronounced (no liaison at all): {{m|fr|quatre-vingt-un}} {{IPAchar|/ka.tʁə.vɛ̃.œ̃/}} not {{IPAchar|*/ka.tʁə.vɛ̃.'''t'''œ̃/}}.
* 80 is {{m|fr|quatre-vingts}} with -s at the end. Therefore the liaison for 80 is {{IPAchar|/s/}} not {{IPAchar|/t/}}. But when used in a compound, the form {{m|fr|quatre-vingt}} (without -s) is used, e.g. {{m|fr|quatre-vingt-un}}.
* A minority of speakers also pronounce the ''-t'' in isolation ({{m|fr||il y en a ving'''t'''}}). This is most common in Switzerland, Belgium, and adjacent regions of eastern France such as Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Champagne-Ardennes, Lorraine, Alsace and Franche-Comte. Some of these speakers pronounce the ''-t'' even before a consonant ({{m|fr||ving'''t''' fois}}).

